they go away.

00:12:44.210 --> 00:12:44.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:12:44.600 --> 00:12:46.590 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: But you can learn to
make peace with things better.

00:12:46.590 --> 00:12:49.310 align:middle line:84%
And as you do it on the little
things, moment to moment, day

00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:51.920 align:middle line:84%
to day, the little common
irritations and frustrations,

00:12:51.920 --> 00:12:54.050 align:middle line:84%
as you turn those
around, as you make

00:12:54.050 --> 00:12:56.227 align:middle line:84%
an internal emotional
shift in yourself

00:12:56.227 --> 00:12:58.310 align:middle line:84%
and don't go through the
same predictable patterns

00:12:58.310 --> 00:13:00.920 align:middle line:84%
all the time, you begin
to accumulate energy.

00:13:00.920 --> 00:13:03.620 align:middle line:84%
That builds up into
what we call resilience.

00:13:03.620 --> 00:13:06.650 align:middle line:84%
And that begins to create a
buffer that makes things easier

00:13:06.650 --> 00:13:07.520 align:middle line:90%
to deal with.

00:13:07.520 --> 00:13:09.920 align:middle line:84%
And even the big things
get easier to deal with.

00:13:09.920 --> 00:13:12.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do you develop
a resource of resilience

00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:13.300 align:middle line:90%
in your body?

00:13:13.300 --> 00:13:15.380 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: Well, you have
to look at it this way.

00:13:15.380 --> 00:13:16.700 align:middle line:90%
We are energy systems.

00:13:16.700 --> 00:13:19.850 align:middle line:84%
We accumulate and deplete
energy, kind of like batteries.

00:13:19.850 --> 00:13:22.230 align:middle line:84%
And we have physical,
mental, emotional energy.

00:13:22.230 --> 00:13:23.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:13:23.030 --> 00:13:25.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: When we experience
a lot of negative emotions,

00:13:25.250 --> 00:13:26.708 align:middle line:84%
we allow those
things to run, we're

00:13:26.708 --> 00:13:28.940 align:middle line:84%
bleeding off a lot of our
emotional energy reserves,

00:13:28.940 --> 00:13:29.600 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:30.475 align:middle line:90%
It' just draining us.

00:13:30.475 --> 00:13:31.558 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Draining us, yeah.

00:13:31.558 --> 00:13:33.142 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTIN: If we stop
that, if we learn

00:13:33.142 --> 00:13:34.670 align:middle line:84%
how to stop that
or at least arrest

00:13:34.670 --> 00:13:37.340 align:middle line:84%
it earlier and then shift it
to where we're experiencing

00:13:37.340 --> 00:13:39.800 align:middle line:84%
something that is more
positive and regenerative,

00:13:39.800 --> 00:13:42.050 align:middle line:84%
then we're adding
energy back into that.

00:13:42.050 --> 00:13:43.730 align:middle line:90%
We're recharging the battery.

00:13:43.730 --> 00:13:45.150 align:middle line:90%
So it becomes simple math.

00:13:45.150 --> 00:13:45.950 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:13:45.950 --> 00:13:48.530 align:middle line:84%
If you add more energy
than you deplete,

00:13:48.530 --> 00:13:50.223 align:middle line:90%
your resilience increases.

00:13:50.223 --> 00:13:51.890 align:middle line:84%
If you continue to
bleed off more energy

00:13:51.890 --> 00:13:54.050 align:middle line:84%
than you're putting
in, resilience

00:13:54.050 --> 00:13:55.360 align:middle line:90%
is going to decrease.

00:13:55.360 --> 00:13:57.180 align:middle line:90%
Resilience is interesting.

00:13:57.180 --> 00:13:59.110 align:middle line:84%
It's not just the
ability to bounce back.

00:13:59.110 --> 00:14:00.777 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the
things that resilience

00:14:00.777 --> 00:14:02.930 align:middle line:84%
is is the ability to
come back quicker.

00:14:02.930 --> 00:14:04.790 align:middle line:84%
But when you have
your resilience level

00:14:04.790 --> 00:14:08.140 align:middle line:84%
up another level, it
does create a buffer

00:14:08.140 --> 00:14:10.850 align:middle line:84%
that does sort of,
in a sense, offer

00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:14.780 align:middle line:84%
some protection from the
stressors that would normally

00:14:14.780 --> 00:14:16.435 align:middle line:90%
get us.

00:14:16.435 --> 00:14:18.060 align:middle line:84%
And it all comes from
what we're doing.

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:20.828 align:middle line:84%
But again, it's the little
things that count today.

00:14:20.828 --> 00:14:22.370 align:middle line:84%
And then when the
big things come up,

00:14:22.370 --> 00:14:23.578 align:middle line:90%
we can deal with them better.

00:14:23.578 --> 00:14:25.477 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you build
resilience by practice?

00:14:25.477 --> 00:14:26.810 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTIN: You do it by practice.

00:14:26.810 --> 00:14:28.610 align:middle line:84%
And you do it by
practicing, again,

00:14:28.610 --> 00:14:30.770 align:middle line:84%
on the things that
you can see and doing

00:14:30.770 --> 00:14:33.530 align:middle line:84%
what you can see
that's real to you

00:14:33.530 --> 00:14:35.510 align:middle line:90%
and learning to make shifts.

00:14:35.510 --> 00:14:38.140 align:middle line:84%
Heroes to me are people that
I watch bend an attitude.

